Drytown first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2010 U.S. census]].<ref name=2010CensusCA/>

The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Drytown had a population of 186. The population density was {{convert|57.1|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Drytown was 84.4% [[White Americans|White]], 0.0% [[African Americans|African American]], 1.1% [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 0.5% [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 1.1% [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 4.3% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 8.6% from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 5.4% of the population.

There were 90 households, out of which 26.7% included children under the age of 18, 45.6% were married-couple households, 4.4% were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 31.1% had a female householder with no partner present, and 18.9% had a male householder with no partner present. 33.3% of households were one person, and 14.4% were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 2.07. There were 52 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (57.8% of all households).

The age distribution was 11.8% under the age of 18, 5.9% aged 18 to 24, 25.3% aged 25 to 44, 23.7% aged 45 to 64, and 33.3% who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 51.5{{nbsp}}years. There were 98 males and 88 females.

There were 101 housing units at an average density of {{convert|31.0|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 90 (89.1%) were occupied. Of these, 63.3% were owner-occupied, and 36.7% were occupied by renters.<ref>{{cite web |title=Drytown CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0619976 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=March 26, 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Drytown CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0619976 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=March 26, 2025}}</ref>

